# Experiment 13: Regime Mining and Failure Subtyping

## Context

I have existing data from Experiments 9–12 of a trajectory geometry study. The setup:
- **Model:** Qwen2.5-0.5B (24 layers)
- **Task:** 300 multi-step arithmetic problems, each run under Direct-answer and Chain-of-Thought (CoT) prompting
- **Hidden states already extracted** for layers 0, 10, 13, 16, 24 across the first 32 generated tokens per response
- **Groups:** G1 (Direct Failure, n=247), G2 (Direct Success, n=53), G3 (CoT Failure, n=77), G4 (CoT Success, n=223)

The existing experiments computed per-trajectory scalar metrics: speed, directional consistency (DC), early curvature, stabilization rate, turning angle, directional autocorrelation, tortuosity, effective dimension, fractal dimension proxy, intrinsic dimension, cosine-to-final slope, distance-to-final slope, early/late distance ratio.

**This experiment runs NO new model inference.** It reuses the already-extracted hidden states and already-computed metrics. All analysis is purely post-hoc statistical/clustering work on existing numpy arrays.

