## Technical Notes

- Use Python with numpy, scipy, scikit-learn, matplotlib, seaborn
- For permutation tests, use k=1000 shuffles
- For Cohen's d, use pooled standard deviation
- For UMAP, use default parameters (n_neighbors=15, min_dist=0.1) — install with pip if needed
- Handle any NaN/inf values by dropping those trajectories and noting how many were excluded
- If any group has fewer than 10 valid samples for a given analysis, note this and interpret cautiously
- Set random seeds (42) for reproducibility